      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The Commanders' rebuild just got a linebacker. After a 5-12 season left them third in the NFC East and staring at the eighth-hardest strength of schedule in football, Washington swung at the draft with purpose - <strong>selecting Sonny Styles with the seventh overall pick to anchor a defense that Dan Quinn is trying to resurrect from the rubble</strong>. Styles arrives as a three-down prospect expected to command the middle, joining a linebacker room already fortified by the offseason addition of Leo Chenal, the Kansas City hybrid who can both attack the line and spy mobile quarterbacks. The Commanders' front office, having mortgaged future picks for aging veterans that didn't move the needle, made six selections total and found value in Antonio Williams and others - earning a solid B grade for their work. Jayden Daniels' offense will carry the load if this team claws back to relevance, but a rebuilt defense with a rookie linebacker and a veteran pass rusher in Chenal gives Quinn something to build on. <strong>Watch whether Styles' three-down versatility can translate immediately and whether this defense can hold up against an unforgiving 2026 schedule</strong>.",
